Wim Pretorius, News24Butcher. (Picture: AFP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria &ndash; A woman had to be airlifted to hospital on Thursday afternoon after her hand got stuck in a mince mixer at a butchery in Pretoria.According to Netcare911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe, the woman sustained serious injuries to her hand, which was still stuck in the mince mixer when the paramedics arrived."After assessing the woman, it was found that she had sustained serious injuries. She was stabilised on scene."She was transported to a hospital in Johannesburg.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.